TEHRAN, Dec. 11 (Xinhua) -- Iran's health ministry on Saturday reported 1,681 new COVID-19 cases, taking the country's total infections to 6,152,524. The pandemic also claimed 58 lives in the past 24 hours, taking the death tally to 130,661, said an update by Iran's Ministry of Health and Medical Education. A total of 5,963,373 people have recovered from the disease or been discharged from hospitals across the country, while 3,126 remain in intensive care units, according to the ministry. By Saturday, 58,595,066 Iranians have received their first vaccine doses, and 49,157,835 of them have taken two jabs. Meanwhile, 2,237,841 people in the country have received their booster doses. The report added that 39,951,481 tests have so far been carried out across the country. Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi said in a meeting of the National Task Force Against Coronavirus on Saturday that the implementation of a COVID-19 smart management plan promotes the protection of the people's lives with more accuracy. The vaccination of children under 12 years of age in the country needs careful study and evaluation, he added. Enditem